class Solution {
    public String reversePrefix(String word, char ch) {
        int idx = word.indexOf(ch);
        if (idx == -1) return word;
        char[] arr = word.toCharArray();
        int l = 0, r = idx;
        while (l < r) {
            char tmp = arr[l];
            arr[l] = arr[r];
            arr[r] = tmp;
            l++; r--;
        }
        return new String(arr);
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single pass to find the first occurrence of ch, then in-place reversal of the prefix using a char array. Minimal extra memory and linear time.

